@txominpelu , I'm not sure if you read the impersonation section in here:
http://www.cloudera.com/content/cloudera/en/documentation/cdh4/v4-3-0/CDH4-Security-Guide/cdh4sg_topic_9_1.html

You could have a model where the user on their dev box need to provide their kerberos creds, and in production the server has superuser creds and impersonates the owner of the task.

@griffinqiu fwiw I went through the same thing yesterday.
The "cleanest" solution I came with was appending my project path to my `$PYTHONPATH` to avoid having to do `sys.path.append` on every single DAG.

Curious what others are doing?
